Structs/Script.html.name: Script
Structs/Script.html.abstract: Many aggregations and some queries allow for the configuration of a script.

Structs/BulkHeader.html.name: BulkHeader
Structs/BulkHeader.html.abstract: Configures the header used for each bulk operation

Structs/ASCIIFoldingFilter.html.name: ASCIIFoldingFilter
Structs/ASCIIFoldingFilter.html.abstract: A token filter of type asciifolding that converts alphabetic, numeric, and symbolic Unicode characters which are not in the first 127 ASCII characters (the Basic Latin Unicode block) into their ASCII equivalents, if one exists.

Structs/ApostropheFilter.html.name: ApostropheFilter
Structs/ApostropheFilter.html.abstract: The apostrophe token filter strips all characters after an apostrophe, including the apostrophe itself.

Structs/ClassicFilter.html.name: ClassicFilter
Structs/ClassicFilter.html.abstract: The classic token filter does optional post-processing of terms that are generated by the classic tokenizer.

Structs/DecimalDigitFilter.html.name: DecimalDigitFilter
Structs/DecimalDigitFilter.html.abstract: The decimal digit token filter folds unicode digits to 0-9

Structs/KStemFilter.html.name: KStemFilter
Structs/KStemFilter.html.abstract: The kstem token filter is a high performance filter for english. All terms must already be lowercased (use lowercase filter) for this filter to work correctly.

Structs/LengthFilter.html.name: LengthFilter
Structs/LengthFilter.html.abstract: A token filter of type length that removes words that are too long or too short for the stream.

Structs/LowercaseFilter.html.name: LowercaseFilter
Structs/LowercaseFilter.html.abstract: A token filter of type lowercase that normalizes token text to lower case.

Structs/PorterStemFilter.html.name: PorterStemFilter
Structs/PorterStemFilter.html.abstract: A token filter of type porter_stem that transforms the token stream as per the Porter stemming algorithm.

Structs/ReverseFilter.html.name: ReverseFilter
Structs/ReverseFilter.html.abstract: A token filter of type reverse that simply reverses each token.

Structs/StandardFilter.html.name: StandardFilter
Structs/StandardFilter.html.abstract: A token filter of type standard that normalizes tokens extracted with the standard tokenizer.

Structs/SynonymFilter.html.name: SynonymFilter
Structs/SynonymFilter.html.abstract: The synonym token filter allows to easily handle synonyms during the analysis process. Synonyms are configured using a configuration file.

Structs/TrimFilter.html.name: TrimFilter
Structs/TrimFilter.html.abstract: The trim token filter trims the whitespace surrounding a token.

Structs/UppercaseFilter.html.name: UppercaseFilter
Structs/UppercaseFilter.html.abstract: A token filter of type uppercase that normalizes token text to upper case.

Structs/HTMLStripCharacterFilter.html.name: HTMLStripCharacterFilter
Structs/HTMLStripCharacterFilter.html.abstract: The HTML strip character filter strips HTML elements from the text and replaces HTML entities with their decoded value (e.g. replacing & with &).

Structs/PatternReplaceCharacterFilter.ht.name: PatternReplaceCharacterFilter
Structs/PatternReplaceCharacterFilter.ht.abstract: The pattern replace character filter uses a regular expression to match characters which should be replaced with the specified replacement string. The replacement string can refer to capture groups in the regular expression.

Structs/MappingCharacterFilter.html.name: MappingCharacterFilter
Structs/MappingCharacterFilter.html.abstract: The mapping character filter accepts a map of keys and values. Whenever it encounters a string of characters that is the same as a key, it replaces them with the value associated with that key.

Structs/ClassicTokenizer.html.name: ClassicTokenizer
Structs/ClassicTokenizer.html.abstract: The classic tokenizer is a grammar based tokenizer that is good for English language documents. This tokenizer has heuristics for special treatment of acronyms, company names, email addresses, and internet host names. However, these rules don’t always work, and the tokenizer doesn’t work well for most languages other than English:

Structs/EdgeNGramTokenizer.html.name: EdgeNGramTokenizer
Structs/EdgeNGramTokenizer.html.abstract: The edge_ngram tokenizer first breaks text down into words whenever it encounters one of a list of specified characters, then it emits N-grams of each word where the start of the N-gram is anchored to the beginning of the word.

Structs/KeywordTokenizer.html.name: KeywordTokenizer
Structs/KeywordTokenizer.html.abstract: The keyword tokenizer is a “noop” tokenizer that accepts whatever text it is given and outputs the exact same text as a single term. It can be combined with token filters to normalise output, e.g. lower-casing email addresses.

Structs/LetterTokenizer.html.name: LetterTokenizer
Structs/LetterTokenizer.html.abstract: The letter tokenizer breaks text into terms whenever it encounters a character which is not a letter. It does a reasonable job for most European languages, but does a terrible job for some Asian languages, where words are not separated by spaces.

Structs/LowercaseTokenizer.html.name: LowercaseTokenizer
Structs/LowercaseTokenizer.html.abstract: The lowercase tokenizer, like the letter tokenizer breaks text into terms whenever it encounters a character which is not a letter, but it also lowercases all terms. It is functionally equivalent to the letter tokenizer combined with the lowercase token filter, but is more efficient as it performs both steps in a single pass.

Structs/NGramTokenizer.html.name: NGramTokenizer
Structs/NGramTokenizer.html.abstract: The ngram tokenizer first breaks text down into words whenever it encounters one of a list of specified characters, then it emits N-grams of each word of the specified length.

Structs/PathHierarchyTokenizer.html.name: PathHierarchyTokenizer
Structs/PathHierarchyTokenizer.html.abstract: The path hierarchy tokenizer takes a hierarchical value like a filesystem path, splits on the path separator, and emits a term for each component in the tree.

Structs/PatternTokenizer.html.name: PatternTokenizer
Structs/PatternTokenizer.html.abstract: The pattern tokenizer uses a regular expression to either split text into terms whenever it matches a word separator, or to capture matching text as terms.

Structs/SimplePatternSplitTokenizer.html.name: SimplePatternSplitTokenizer
Structs/SimplePatternSplitTokenizer.html.abstract: The simple pattern split tokenizer uses a regular expression to split the input into terms at pattern matches. The set of regular expression features it supports is more limited than the pattern tokenizer, but the tokenization is generally faster.

Structs/SimplePatternTokenizer.html.name: SimplePatternTokenizer
Structs/SimplePatternTokenizer.html.abstract: The simple pattern tokenizer uses a regular expression to capture matching text as terms. The set of regular expression features it supports is more limited than the pattern tokenizer, but the tokenization is generally faster.

Structs/StandardTokenizer.html.name: StandardTokenizer
Structs/StandardTokenizer.html.abstract: The standard tokenizer provides grammar based tokenization (based on the Unicode Text Segmentation algorithm, as specified in Unicode Standard Annex #29) and works well for most languages.

Structs/ThaiTokenizer.html.name: ThaiTokenizer
Structs/ThaiTokenizer.html.abstract: The thai tokenizer segments Thai text into words, using the Thai segmentation algorithm included with Java. Text in other languages in general will be treated the same as the standard tokenizer.

Structs/UAXURLEmailTokenizer.html.name: UAXURLEmailTokenizer
Structs/UAXURLEmailTokenizer.html.abstract: The uax url email tokenizer is like the standard tokenizer except that it recognises URLs and email addresses as single tokens.

Structs/WhitespaceTokenizer.html.name: WhitespaceTokenizer
Structs/WhitespaceTokenizer.html.abstract: The whitespace tokenizer breaks text into terms whenever it encounters a whitespace character.

Structs/MinAggregation.html.name: MinAggregation
Structs/MinAggregation.html.abstract: A single-value metrics aggregation that keeps track and returns the minimum

Structs/SumAggregation.html.name: SumAggregation
Structs/SumAggregation.html.abstract: A single-value metrics aggregation that sums up numeric values that are

Structs/StatsAggregation.html.name: StatsAggregation
Structs/StatsAggregation.html.abstract: A multi-value metrics aggregation that computes stats over numeric values

Structs/MaxAggregation.html.name: MaxAggregation
Structs/MaxAggregation.html.abstract: A single-value metrics aggregation that keeps track and returns the maximum

Structs/AvgAggregation.html.name: AvgAggregation
Structs/AvgAggregation.html.abstract: A single-value metrics aggregation that computes the average of numeric values

Structs/GeoCentroidAggregation.html.name: GeoCentroidAggregation
Structs/GeoCentroidAggregation.html.abstract: A metric aggregation that computes the weighted centroid from all coordinate

Structs/GeoBoundsAggregation.html.name: GeoBoundsAggregation
Structs/GeoBoundsAggregation.html.abstract: A metric aggregation that computes the bounding box containing all geo_point values for a field.

Structs/TopHitsAggregation.html.name: TopHitsAggregation
Structs/TopHitsAggregation.html.abstract: A top_hits metric aggregator keeps track of the most relevant document being

Structs/CardinalityAggregation.html.name: CardinalityAggregation
Structs/CardinalityAggregation.html.abstract: A single-value metrics aggregation that calculates an approximate count of

Structs/ValueCountAggregation.html.name: ValueCountAggregation
Structs/ValueCountAggregation.html.abstract: A single-value metrics aggregation that counts the number of values that are

Structs/ExtendedStatsAggregation.html.name: ExtendedStatsAggregation
Structs/ExtendedStatsAggregation.html.abstract: A multi-value metrics aggregation that computes stats over numeric values

Structs/TermsAggregation.html.name: TermsAggregation
Structs/TermsAggregation.html.abstract: A multi-bucket value source based aggregation where buckets are dynamically built - one per unique value.

Structs/SearchContainer.html.name: SearchContainer
Structs/SearchContainer.html.abstract: This is the topmost container for specifying a query.

Structs/BoolQuery.html.name: BoolQuery
Structs/BoolQuery.html.abstract: A query that matches documents matching boolean combinations of other queries.

Structs/CommonTerms.html.name: CommonTerms
Structs/CommonTerms.html.abstract: The common terms query is a modern alternative to stopwords which improves the

Structs/Exists.html.name: Exists
Structs/Exists.html.abstract: Returns documents that have at least one non-null value in the original field.

Structs/Fuzzy.html.name: Fuzzy
Structs/Fuzzy.html.abstract: The fuzzy query uses similarity based on Levenshtein edit distance. The fuzzy

Structs/IDs.html.name: IDs
Structs/IDs.html.abstract: Filters documents that only have the provided ids.

Structs/Match.html.name: Match
Structs/Match.html.abstract: Match queries accept text/numerics/dates, analyzes them, and constructs a query.

Structs/MatchAll.html.name: MatchAll
Structs/MatchAll.html.abstract: The most simple query, which matches all documents, giving them all a score of 1.0

Structs/MatchNone.html.name: MatchNone
Structs/MatchNone.html.abstract: This is the inverse of the MatchAll query, which matches no documents.

Structs/MatchPhrase.html.name: MatchPhrase
Structs/MatchPhrase.html.abstract: The MatchPhrase query analyzes the text and creates a phrase query out of the analyzed text.

Structs/MatchPhrasePrefix.html.name: MatchPhrasePrefix
Structs/MatchPhrasePrefix.html.abstract: The MatchPhrasePrefix is the same as match_phrase, except that it allows for prefix matches on the last term in the text.

Structs/MultiMatch.html.name: MultiMatch
Structs/MultiMatch.html.abstract: The MultiMatch query builds on the MatchQuery to allow multi-field queries.

Structs/Prefix.html.name: Prefix
Structs/Prefix.html.abstract: Matches documents that have fields containing terms with a specified prefix

Structs/Query.html.name: Query
Structs/Query.html.abstract: A Query starts the query portion of a search to be executed (as opposed to an Aggregation).

Structs/Range.html.name: Range
Structs/Range.html.abstract: Matches documents with fields that have terms within a certain range. The type

Structs/Regexp.html.name: Regexp
Structs/Regexp.html.abstract: The regexp query allows you to use regular expression term queries. See

Structs/ScriptQuery.html.name: ScriptQuery
Structs/ScriptQuery.html.abstract: A query allowing to define scripts as queries. They are typically used in a filter context.

Structs/Term.html.name: Term
Structs/Term.html.abstract: The Term query finds documents that contain the exact term specified in the inverted index.

Structs/Terms.html.name: Terms
Structs/Terms.html.abstract: Filters documents that have fields that match any of the provided terms (not analyzed).

Structs/Wildcard.html.name: Wildcard
Structs/Wildcard.html.abstract: Matches documents that have fields matching a wildcard expression (not

Structs/GeoPolygon.html.name: GeoPolygon
Structs/GeoPolygon.html.abstract: A query allowing to define scripts as queries. They are typically used in a filter context.
